<section>
  <h2>Accessibility</h2>
  <p>Each <code>&lt;map-area&gt;</code> generates a focusable anchor element (<code>&lt;a&gt;</code> when <code>href</code> is set, <code>&lt;button&gt;</code> otherwise) with <code>aria-label</code> matching the area&rsquo;s <code>label</code> attribute. The SVG overlay is <code>aria-hidden</code> &mdash; it handles only pointer hit-testing. The tooltip uses <code>role=&quot;tooltip&quot;</code> and <code>aria-live=&quot;polite&quot;</code> for screen reader announcements.</p>
  <p>The host element uses <code>role=&quot;group&quot;</code> with an <code>aria-label</code> derived from the image alt text.</p>
</section>

<section>
  <h2>Progressive Enhancement</h2>
  <code-block language="html" show-lines label="Without JavaScript">{{ fallbackCode | escape }}</code-block>
</section>

<section>
  <h2>Touch Behaviour</h2>
  <p>On touch devices with <code>tooltip=&quot;hover&quot;</code>, a two-tap pattern is used: the first tap shows the tooltip, the second tap navigates (if <code>href</code> is set). For <code>tooltip=&quot;click&quot;</code>, tapping toggles the tooltip on/off. Press <kbd>Escape</kbd> or tap elsewhere to dismiss.</p>
</section>

